Lane Name Meaning

The name Lane is an English name that means “pathway” or “a strip of land”

Origins of the Name Lane

The name Lane is of English origin and is a surname that was originally used to denote a person who lived near a lane or pathway. The name is derived from the Old English word “lán,” which means “a strip of land.”

Popularity of the Name Lane

In recent years, the name Lane has become increasingly popular as a given name for boys in the United States and other English-speaking countries. In the United States, it has risen from outside the top 1000 names in the early 2000s to being a top 500 name in 2021.

Lane is a classic and timeless name that is perfect for parents who are looking for a name that is simple and understated. With its strong roots in English history, Lane is a name that is sure to stand the test of time.

Famous Lanes

Throughout history, there have been many notable people with the name Lane, including actors, athletes, and politicians. Some of the most famous Lanes include:

Lane Kiffin, an American football coach

Lane Smith, an American actor

Lane Pryce, a character from the television series “Mad Men”

Final Thoughts on the Name Lane

The name Lane is full of history and meaning, and is perfect for parents who are looking for a name that has a story to tell. Whether you’re a parent looking for a classic and timeless name for your son, or you’re just a fan of all things simple and understated, the name Lane is the perfect choice!
